President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation on November 9, 2018, in honor of Veterans Day. He highlighted the significance of November 11th, which marks the 100th anniversary of the Armistice that ended World War I. The proclamation emphasized the sacrifices made by American service members in the war and the importance of honoring their heroism. President Trump also mentioned the VA MISSION Act of 2018, which provides reforms to the Department of Veterans Affairs and ensures veterans have access to quality healthcare. He expressed gratitude to veterans and their families for their selflessness and love of country. The proclamation called on all Americans to recognize and support veterans through public ceremonies and private thoughts and prayers. It also encouraged the display of the American flag and participation in patriotic activities.